    "narrative": "Our top-tier plays today are headlined by **Cal Raleigh** (70.13) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (69.13), both of whom benefit from favorable matchups against pitchers with xERAs above 4.40. **Cal Raleigh** receives a significant boost from a dynamic platoon advantage and a premium spot in the two-hole, while **Geraldo Perdomo**\u2019s elite sprint speed projection against the porous arm of M\u00e1rquez makes him a vital catalyst for our SB category. **Will Smith** (68.08) and **Bryson Stott** (66.28) round out our strongest starts; **Bryson Stott** is particularly well-positioned given a strong platoon edge against Elder, while **Will Smith** gains additional upside from wind-aided conditions that push his daily efficiency into elite territory despite the uncertainty of his pending lineup spot.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s card was leaving **Yainer Diaz** (51.72) on the bench. He hovered just outside our starting threshold, but ultimately, his projected spot at the bottom of the order (-6%) and the optimizer\u2019s preference for the higher ceiling offered by **Taylor Ward**\u2014who benefits from a massive park factor boost and a top-of-the-order designation against Crochet\u2014pushed **Yainer Diaz** into the reserve slot. We are also managing significant risk with **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Taylor Ward**, as both face the elite arm of Crochet. While **Taylor Ward** maintains a strong 59.23 score due to his leadoff duties and park environment, **Jeremiah Jackson** remains a marginal play (45.72) that we are only deploying due to his high-leverage potential in a hitter-friendly venue. \n\nFinally, managers should monitor the lineups for **Will Smith**, **Bryson Stott**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, and **Gavin Sheets** closely, as the \"Lineup Pending\" designation introduces non-trivial variance to our efficiency projections. While **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (59.86) faces a tough outing against Gausman, his intrinsic value remains high enough to warrant a start despite a poor historical BvP. We are keeping a close eye on the late-game stolen base opportunities for **Jung Hoo Lee** against Eury P\u00e9rez, as that 100% SB delivery factor for the opposition remains a critical component of our strategy to secure scarce counting stats today.",
